sName":"mb-3 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-slate-400","children":"Key statistics in this story"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"grid grid-cols-1 gap-3 sm:grid-cols-2","children":[["$","div","murder-rate",{"className":"card p-4","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"text-xs text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400","children":"Murder Cases"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-1 font-mono text-2xl font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white","children":"26,232"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-0.5 text-xs text-slate-400","children":["from 2022/23"," · ","SAPS"]}]]}],["$","div","crime-contact",{"className":"card p-4","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"text-xs text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400","children":"Contact Crimes (Total)"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-1 font-mono text-2xl font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white","children":"561,947"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-0.5 text-xs text-slate-400","children":["from 2022/23"," · ","SAPS"]}]]}],["$","div","crime-robbery",{"className":"card p-4","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"text-xs text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400","children":"Robbery with Aggravating Circumstances"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-1 font-mono text-2xl font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white","children":"162,618"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-0.5 text-xs text-slate-400","children":["from 2022/23"," · ","SAPS"]}]]}]]}]]}],["$","article",null,{"className":"prose-story","children":[["$","section","what-saps-publishes",{"id":"what-saps-publishes","className":"mb-10 scroll-mt-24","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"heading-display mb-4 text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white","children":"What SAPS actually publishes"}],[["$","p","0",{"className":"mb-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300","children":"Each September, the South African Police Service releases crime statistics covering the April-to-March financial year. The data covers crimes reported to police — which is not the same as crimes committed."}],["$","p","1",{"className":"mb-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300","children":"Under-reporting is a persistent issue. Surveys suggest that many crimes, particularly sexual offences, domestic violence, and theft, are significantly under-reported. Fear of police, social stigma, lack of transport to a police station, and low faith in the criminal justice system all reduce reporting rates."}],["$","p","2",{"className":"mb-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300","children":"With that caveat in mind, the SAPS data is the most comprehensive official record available and remains the essential reference point for tracking trends over time."}]],["$","blockquote",null,{"className":"my-6 border-l-4 border-brand-400 pl-5","children":["$","p",null,{"className":"text-lg font-medium italic leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-200","children":["\"","Crime statistics count crimes reported to police — not crimes committed.","\""]}]}],[]]}],["$","section","murder",{"id":"murder","className":"mb-10 scroll-mt-24","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"heading-display mb-4 text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white","children":"Murder: the most reliable indicator"}],[["$","p","0",{"className":"mb-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300","children":"Murder is considered the most reliable crime statistic internationally because bodies are difficult to conceal and the police almost always record them. The 2023/24 figure of 26,232 murders — a 4.6% decline from the 27,494 in 2022/23 — is therefore meaningful."}],["$","p","1",{"className":"mb-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300","children":"This equates to approximately 72 murders per day, or a rate of 41.9 per 100,000 population. For context, the global average is around 6 per 100,000. South Africa's rate is more than six times higher."}],["$","p","2",{"className":"mb-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300","children":"Gauteng, KwaZulu-Natal, and the Western Cape account for the majority of murders. The Cape Flats area of Cape Town — plagued by gang violence — has been a persistent hotspot. The SAPS has deployed the military in several Western Cape communities in recent years as part of anti-gang operations."}]],"$undefined",[["$","div",null,{"className":"my-6 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 dark:border-slate-700 dark:bg-slate-900 flex flex-col gap-3 sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:gap-6","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex-shrink-0","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"font-mono text-4xl font-medium tabular-nums text-slate-900 dark:text-white","children":"26,232"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-1 flex items-center gap-1.5","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-1 rounded-full px-2 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium bg-brand-50 text-brand-700 dark:bg-brand-950/40 dark:text-brand-300","children":[["$","svg",null,{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":11,"height":11,"viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","strokeWidth":2,"strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","className":"lucide lucide-trending-down","children":[["$","polyline","1r2t7k",{"points":"22 17 13.5 8.5 8.5 13.5 2 7"}],["$","polyline","11uiuu",{"points":"16 17 22 17 22 11"}],"$undefined"]}],"4.6","%"]}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xs text-slate-400","children":"from 2022/23"}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"hidden h-12 w-px bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-800 sm:block"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"flex-1 min-w-0","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white","children":"Murder Cases"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-1 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 line-clamp-2","children":"Total murder cases reported nationally for the 2023/24 financial year (April 2023 – March 2024). This is the first decline in four years, equating to approximately 72 murders per day. The rate is 41.9 per 100,000 population."}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-2 text-xs text-slate-400","children":["SAPS"," · Updated ","20 September 2024"]}]]}]]}]]]}],["$","section","contact-crime",{"id":"contact-crime","className":"mb-10 scroll-mt-24","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"heading-display mb-4 text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white","children":"Contact crime and what drives it"}],[["$","p","0",{"className":"mb-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300","children":"Contact crimes — those involving physical contact between perpetrator and victim, including assault, robbery, and murder — totalled 561,947 in 2023/24. This was a 4% decline from 2022/23 and the first reduction in several years."}],["$","p","1",{"className":"mb-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300","children":"Robbers with aggravating circumstances — carjackings, house robberies, bank robberies — declined 3.1% to 162,618 cases. This is a category that particularly affects middle-class and business communities and tends to receive significant media attention."}],["$","p","2",{"className":"mb-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300","children":"Research consistently links crime levels to unemployment, inequality, poverty, and weak state capacity. South Africa scores highly on all these risk factors, which is why its crime rates remain elevated even during periods of improving economic conditions."}]],"$undefined",[["$","div",null,{"className":"my-6 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 dark:border-slate-700 dark:bg-slate-900 flex flex-col gap-3 sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:gap-6","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex-shrink-0","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"font-mono text-4xl font-medium tabular-nums text-slate-900 dark:text-white","children":"561,947"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-1 flex items-center gap-1.5","ch